\vspace{10 mm}
\begin{center}
{\Large\bf Null-Brane Solutions in Supergravities}
\vspace{30 mm}

{\large
Nobuyoshi Ohta\footnote{e-mail address: ohta@phys.sci.osaka-u.ac.jp}}\\
\vspace{10 mm}
{\em Department of Physics, Osaka University,
Toyonaka, Osaka 560-0043, Japan}
\end{center}
\vspace{15 mm}
\centerline{{\bf{Abstract}}}
\vspace{5 mm}

We find a new class of time-dependent brane solutions in supergravities
in arbitrary dimensions $D$. These are general intersecting light-like
branes (null-branes), and their superposition and intersection rules
are obtained. This is achieved by directly solving bosonic
field equations for supergravity coupled to a dilaton and antisymmetric
tensor fields. We discuss their possible significance.

\
